Cell.Text: When Red Mountain erupted almost two hundred years ago, it flung ash and rocks for hundreds of miles. | Among the debris were heart stones. Even two centuries later, they still smolder with the heat of the mountain. | These are the molten rocks that lay next to the Heart of Lorkhan for millennia. Some vestige of its power must have seeped into them. | I do know that heart stones sometimes raise ash spawn from the bits of bone buried in the nearby ash.

Node.Caption: DLC2TelMithrynHeartStoneTopic: What is a heart stone?

Cell.Text: I hear you know where to find Black Books.
<<Shared>> You refer to the tomes of esoteric knowledge that old Hermaeus Mora has scattered throughout the world?
S|This is a Telvanni tower. It's my citadel, grown from the spores of the giant fungus trees found in Morrowind. | Back in the homeland, there are other Telvanni wizards that have them as well.

Node.Caption: DLC2TelMithrynNelothsTowerTopic: What is this building?

Cell.Text: [S] S|You again. Didn't I see you in Raven Rock?
[S] S|I don't recall inviting you into my tower. I do hope you make this worth my while.

Node.Caption: DLC2TelMithrynGreetPC

Cell.Text: Yes. That was a lifetime ago. | I was just a young girl when Red Mountain erupted. Master Neloth was already old. | My mother put me on a boat to Skyrim. The last time I ever saw her, she was standing on the dock as my ship sailed away.

Node.Caption: DLC2DialogueTelMithrynElyneaTopic: Did you come here from Morrowind?

Cell.Text: For now, not much. But in a few decades when I return to Vvardenfell, you would be seen as Morrowind nobility. | In the mean time, we would keep a bed and chest here for you.

Node.Caption: DLC2TelMithrynTelvanniMembershipTopic: What does it mean to be a member of your house?

Cell.Text: You've never heard of the great houses of Morrowind? | House Telvanni is the house of the master wizard, one of the ruling houses of Morrowind. | Master Neloth is one of the oldest and most respected members of House Telvanni.

Node.Caption: DLC2TelMithrynTelvanniHouses: Telvanni? What are the Telvanni?

Cell.Text: Not so much with as for. | I am Master Neloth's apprentice. He's teaching me the art of sorcery.

Node.Caption: DLC2TelMithrynWorkWithNelothTopic: Do you work with Neloth?

Cell.Text: Um. Well, he is a very great wizard. It's a great honor for him to have taken me as his apprentice. | To be honest, it's horrible. He's very unpleasant and hardly teaches me anything. Sometimes he uses me in his experiments. | Even so, I pick up a lot from just watching him.

Node.Caption: DLC2TelMithrynWhereIsNelothTopic: Is Master Neloth a good teacher?

Cell.Text: [S] This is Master Neloth's tower. He's a Telvanni Wizard.

Node.Caption: DLC2TelMithrynTalvasTowerTopic: What is this place?

Cell.Text: G|I am likely the greatest wizard you will ever meet. | Who else do you think could create a staff enchanter? | If you make yourself useful around here, I might just let you use it.

Node.Caption: DLC2TelMithrynWizard: You must be a very powerful wizard.

Cell.Text: Of course you have. | Everyone has heard of the master wizards of Morrowind. | We are one of the great houses that rule Morrowind.

Node.Caption: DLC2TelMithrynKnowTelvanni: I've heard of the House Telvanni of Morrowind.

Cell.Text: G|Savros? Ha! He wouldn't be fit to be my apprentice. | Of course he does have a knack for wards that would be handy to learn. | If you see him, let him know that I might be willing to take him on as my apprentice. For a price of course.

Node.Caption: DLC2TelMithrynWinterhold: You must be almost as powerful as Savros Aren of Winterhold.

Cell.Text: G|Winterhold? That small college that is falling into the Sea of Ghosts? | You're the one that recovered the Staff of Magnus. Impressive. | Talvas should finish his apprenticeship in a couple of decades. Come see me then. I think I could teach you a trick or two.

Node.Caption: DLC2TelMithrynArchmage: As the Archmage of Winterhold, you and I should share our secrets.

Cell.Text: The Telvanni are the master wizards of Morrowind. | The greatest of us grow magical towers like this one from the mighty fungus trees. | Together we form House Telvanni, one of the great houses of Morrowind. The great houses rule what is left of our once proud nation.

Node.Caption: DLC2DialogueTelMithrynHouses: Telvanni? What are the Telvanni?

Cell.Text: Yes. I haven't been idle while this fascinating madness engulfed Solstheim. | But my book isn't what you're looking for. I'm quite sure it is unconnected with this Miraak. | But I do know where to find a Black Book that can help you.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothIntroC1: You have a Black Book?

Cell.Text: Yes, I do. I haven't been able to get it, though. But maybe together we can unlock the secrets the Dwemer left behind.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothIntroC3: So you know where to find this Black Book? The one connected with Miraak?

Cell.Text: Forbidden knowledge was somewhat of a specialty of the dwarves, eh? You don't think they would just leave it alone, do you?

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothIntroD1: The Dwemer? What do they have to do with this?

Cell.Text: [S] G|It seems the ancient Dwemer discovered this book and took it to study. | I found their "reading room" in the ruins of Nchardak. The book is there, but it's sealed in a protective case which I wasn't able to open. | But perhaps the two of us together will be able to get at the book. | To Nchardak, then. Follow me.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothIntroFinal

Cell.Text: Oh, it clearly is not associated with the same power that has overtaken the island. | And I'm not talking about Hermaeus Mora. These Black Books are all his, of course. | No, what you're looking for is a specific book. Presumably because Miraak's power derives from it.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothIntroC2: Why won't the book you have here help me?

Cell.Text: I'm afraid it isn't that simple. If it was, I would have the book already.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothIntroD2: Just tell me where the book is and I'll go get it.

Cell.Text: Is this somehow connected to your search for Miraak?
What could you know of them?

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothIntroA0: That's right.

Cell.Text: [S] Found one? Yes, and you read it, too, didn't you? Don't try to deny it, you've got the look. I can see it now. | Dangerous knowledge is still knowledge and therefore useful. Usually turns out to be the most useful, in my experience.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothIntroA1: I found a Black Book. I need to find more.

Cell.Text: Now that is a dangerous path indeed. Hermaeus Mora gives nothing away for free. | You may end up like Miraak, of course. Two power-mad Dragonborn. It could be very interesting.
Miraak? The one all the townsfolk are always chanting about?

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothIntroB1: I have to know what Miraak knows if I want to stop him.

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> You refer to the tomes of esoteric knowledge that old Hermaeus Mora has scattered throughout the world?
Do you know where I can find another Black Book?
Oh yes. They're not hard to locate once you know how to look for them. I have one here that I've been using to locate more.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothIntroTopic: I hear you know where to find Black Books.

Cell.Text: Well, I knew something connected with Hermaeus Mora was spreading its influence across the island. | I wasn't sure that it was in fact the same entity as this legendary namesake of the central temple. Although the villagers seem quite convinced.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothIntroB2: Yes. You may have noticed he's trying to return to Solstheim.

Cell.Text: S|You didn't know? Hmm, I thought it was obvious.
What do the Black Books have to do with Hermaeus Mora?

<<Shared>> Hermaeus Mora has always tried to seduce mortals into his service with the lure of forbidden knowledge. | Where the Black Books actually came from... no one really knows. Some appear to have been written far in the past, others might be from the future. | Apparently time is more malleable if you're the Daedric Prince of fate and destiny.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothIntroHM: The Black Books have something to do with Hermaeus Mora?

Cell.Text: I've dealt with Hermaeus Mora before. I've read the Oghma Infinium.

Have you? The actual Oghma Infinium? That's... I've searched for it myself for many years without success... | Well then, you should know better than anyone that Hermaeus Mora is not to be trifled with. | But he is subtler than most of the other Daedric Princes, as you would expect of the prince of knowledge and fate. | You seem to have escaped the fate of many who find themselves ensnared forever by the lure of his secrets. Or... perhaps not.

<<Shared>> If you have to ask that, you'd probably be best leaving his books to wiser heads than yours. | Like all Daedric Princes, he's not to be trifled with. But he is subtler than most of his ilk, appropriate for the prince of knowledge and fate. | Many scholars and loremasters have been ensnared by the lure of learning the secrets that only Hermaeus Mora possesses. | But don't worry. I have no intention of joining them in their endless search through the infinite halls of Apocrypha.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothIntroWhoIsHM: Who is Hermaeus Mora?
